The Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, has paid a visit to the family of Ifeanyi Okereke.  Ifeanyi Okereke is the newspaper vendor who was shot dead by one of Gbajabiamila’s security aides in Abuja last Thursday, November 18. Gbajabiamila condoled with the wife and family of the late vendor at Kwata village, Madalla-Suleja, Niger State and pledged to ensure justice is served. After the incident, the speaker released a statement in which he pledged to cater to the wife and the immediate family he left behind. He also identified the security aide as Abdullahi Hassan, whom the SSS has since detained. Source Following the death of Ifeanyi Okereke, his sister has been reduced to tears. Recall that the Abuja vendor was killed by a security aide to the House of Reps speaker Femi Gbajabiamila. In a video shared by the BBC, the late vendors sister can be seen lamenting his death, as… November 20, 2020 In "News" The Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, has described the killing of a newspaper vendor in Abuja by one of the security details as horrible, saying he is distraught by the incident. Gbajabiamila, in a statement he personally signed and issued in the early hours of Friday, said… November 20, 2020 In "News" Newspapers vendors in the Federal Capital Territory on Friday protested the killing of their colleagues, Ifeanyi Elechi, who was shot dead on Thursday by a security aide to the Speaker, House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila. The vendors who were carrying placards, demanded justice, insisting that the errant operative who is… November 20, 2020 In "News"